Participants will be randomized to either (1) writing about dental pain or (2) writing about 
death. This is a between-participants design, and it will be assigned randomly by 
Qualtrics. However, the variable of cultural background (European American versus 
Asian American) is not randomly assigned. To ensure roughly equal cell sizes, we will 
choose the option in Qualtrics that allows for equal cell sizes (i.e., among the Asian 
American participants, equal cell sizes in dental pain versus death writing conditions, 
and among the European American participants, equal cell sizes in dental pain versus 
death writing conditions.  
 
 

 
