The original paper did not mention whether the study was conducted online or in the 
laboratory. However, given the data of publication (2011) and the age of participants 
(20-22 years old), it’s likely that participants (1) were college students and (2) participated 
in the lab as a part of a participant pool. We plan to conduct the study online, which we 
presume is a difference from the original study. We anticipate that this difference does 
not have a high likelihood of affecting the results, but it is worth pointing out this 
potential for discrepancy.  
 
Another difference worth noting is that we plan on conducting the study in the summer 
and fall of 2020, during the coronavirus pandemic. It’s possible that writing about death 
carries different psychological meanings at a time of widespread disease and fear.  
 
 
 

 
